<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/3123a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-05">November 5,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2726. American interests Far East—repatriation. The United States
                                Government would like to make another exchange with the Japanese
                                Government to cover 1500 Americans for 1500 Japanese. Will you
                                please present the matter to the attention of the Japanese
                                Government and advise Department of their attitude. If their reply
                                is favorable it might be possible for the <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> to leave New York about February 1.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>